result.execSummary:
The defendant Giau Van Le was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Giau Van Le in court.  Kevin M. Osborne appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Case recalled at 1:41 pm. Bail previously refunded to posted but never received due to a change of address. Check is stopped and cash bail to be applied to restitution and costs.

Defendant Giau Van Le in court.  Timothy F. Westphal appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant is residing in Texas and would like to find a way to resolve this matter.  Court passes matter to allow defendant to review the criminal complaint and pretrial offer.  Case recalled at 10:33.  Defendant would like to resolve this matter today.  Court passes matter to allow defendant to complete the appropriate paperwork.  Case recalled at 11:44.  Defendant would like to proceed with a change of plea at this time.  Defendant enters an Alford guilty plea to Count 1.  Court finds defendant guilty.  Counts 2 and 3 dismissed and read in.

Court orders the following:
- 5 months Huber with standard release conditions. STAYED
- 1 year Probation.  Probation may be transferred to Texas.
- Court costs of $243.00 to be paid as a Condition of Probation
- Restitution of $242.95 to be paid to Sergeant Lesniewski
- DNA Surcharge waived
- DNA Sample waived
- Conditions of Probation:  No violent contact with victim.  No contact with former neighbor.  DV Counseling to be determined by Agent.
CONDITION TIME: 30 days - NON WORKING HOURS WITH STANDARD RELEASE CONDITIONS - STAYED for use by Agent.

Cash bail previously posted to be refunded to poster.  Defendant is not to have any violent contact with witness listed in the criminal complaint.    Absolute sobriety, defendant is not to possess or consume any alcohol.  Defendant is not to use/possess any controlled substances without a valid prescription and take as prescribed.

Defendant Giau Van Le in court.   District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court advises of right to an attorney.  State has no offer to amend charges.    NOT GUILTY PLEA ENTERED BY COURT.
